{# sec-5 : As-Is Analysis (Marcus) - organization + standard objects.
   L'organization est rendue en table key-value avec chips pour les listes
   (permission_sets_standard, profiles_standard). Cles humanisees via le filtre
   'humanize' (snake_case -> espaces). L'ordre des cles dans organization n'est
   pas garanti par PostgreSQL JSONB, on definit l'ordre canonique du rendu de
   reference ci-dessous. #}
{% set ORG_ORDER = ['edition', 'api_version', 'release', 'custom_objects',
                    'apex_classes', 'apex_triggers', 'flows', 'lightning_pages',
                    'permission_sets_custom', 'permission_sets_standard',
                    'profiles_standard'] %}<section id='sec-5' class='block'>
<div class='act'><span class='act-num'>— Scene V</span><span class='act-sep'></span><span class='act-tag'>Artifact 05</span></div><h1 class='sec-h1'><span>As-Is Analysis</span> <em class='brass'>(Marcus — Solution Architect)</em></h1>
<p>Marcus inspected the existing Salesforce org to baseline what is already in place before designing the target architecture.</p>
<h2 id='sub-5-1' class='sec-h2'><span>5.1 Organization</span></h2>
<table class='tbl'>
{% set first_key = ORG_ORDER[0] %}<thead><tr>
<th><strong>{{ first_key | humanize }}</strong></th>
<th>{{ as_is.organization[first_key] }}</th>
</tr></thead>
<tbody>
{% for key in ORG_ORDER[1:] %}{% if key in as_is.organization %}{% set val = as_is.organization[key] %}<tr>
<td><strong>{{ key | humanize }}</strong></td>
{% if val is iterable and val is not string %}<td class='td-json'><div class='chiprow'>{% for item in val %}<span class='chip'>{{ item }}</span>{% if not loop.last %} {% endif %}{% endfor %}</div></td>
{% else %}<td>{{ val }}</td>
{% endif %}</tr>
{% endif %}{% endfor %}</tbody></table>
<h2 id='sub-5-2' class='sec-h2'><span>5.2 Standard Objects in Org</span> <em class='brass'>({{ as_is.standard_objects | length }})</em></h2>
<table class='tbl'>
<thead><tr>
<th><strong>Object</strong></th>
<th><strong>Custom fields</strong></th>
<th><strong>Notes</strong></th>
</tr></thead>
<tbody>
{% for obj in as_is.standard_objects %}<tr>
<td><strong>{{ obj.name }}</strong></td>
<td>{{ obj.custom_fields_count }}</td>
<td>{{ obj.description }}</td>
</tr>
{% endfor %}</tbody></table>
</section>
